     1                        ;**************************************************************************************************
     2                        ;*                                                                                                *
     3                        ;*                  Utility program for the MicroDrive PATA Adapter 0.91                          *
     4                        ;*                                                                                                *
     5                        ;*                                                                                                *
     6                        ;*       This Utility provides functions to identify, test and edit a MicroDrive when present     *
     7                        ;*         The following functions are provided:                                                  *
     8                        ;*           - Identify MicroDrive: Vendor String, Device Serial, LBA Count in Hex/Decimal)       *
     9                        ;*           - Read any LBA into memory and display contents in Hex/ASCII                         *
    10                        ;*           - Write any LBA from memory and display contents in Hex/ASCII                        *
    11                        ;*           - Read Full LBA count sequentially or staggered                                      *
    12                        ;*           - Write Full LBA count sequentially or staggered                                     *
    13                        ;*           - Benchmark reading and writing of 32MB of sequential data                           *
    14                        ;*           - Transfer a block of memory to a block of Disc for writing the OS image             *
    15                        ;*         - Note: Write pattern is $55AA for Sequential Write                                    *
    16                        ;*                 Write pattern is User defined for Write Benchmark                              *
    17                        ;*                                                                                                *
    18                        ;**************************************************************************************************
    19                                PL      66      ;Page Length
    20                                PW      132     ;Page Width (# of char/line)
    21                                CHIP    W65C02S ;Enable WDC 65C02 instructions
    22                                PASS1   OFF     ;Set ON when used for debug
    23                                INCLIST ON      ;Set ON for listing Include files
    24                        ;**************************************************************************************************
    25                        ;
    26                        ; C02BIOS Version 5.1 is the supported BIOS level for this utility!
    27                        ;
    28                        ; This BIOS version also use a common source file for constants and variables used by
    29                        ; both. This just simplifies keeping both code pieces in sync.
    30                        ;
