  1336                        ;DECIN subroutine: request 1 - 10 DECIMAL digit input from terminal, followed by [RETURN].
  1337                        ; [ESCAPE] aborts, [BACKSPACE] erases last keystroke.
  1338                        ; Convert input to BCD and HEX then store both results as follows:
  1339                        ; Converted 10 digit (5 byte) BCD value will be contained in variables DEC0AND1 through DEC8AND9:
  1340                        ;  DEC0AND1 ($E5) Two most significant BCD digits
  1341                        ;  DEC2AND3 ($E6)
  1342                        ;  DEC4AND5 ($E7)
  1343                        ;  DEC6AND7 ($E8)
  1344                        ;  DEC8AND9 ($E9) Two least significant BCD digits
  1345                        ; Converted 8 digit (4 byte) HEX value will be contained in variables HEX0AND1 through HEX6AND7:
  1346                        ;  HEX0AND1 ($E1) Two most significant HEX digits
  1347                        ;  HEX2AND3 ($E2)
  1348                        ;  HEX4AND5 ($E3)
  1349                        ;  HEX6AND7 ($E4) Two least significant HEX digits
  1350                        ; NOTE1: If a DECIMAL value greater than 4,294,967,295 ($FFFFFFFF) is entered,
  1351                        ;  1 or 2 asterisks (*) will be sent to the terminal following the inputted digits.
  1352                        ;  This is to indicate that an overflow in the HEX accumulator has occured.
  1353                        ;  (the BCDTOHEX subroutine's HEX accumulator "rolls over" to zero when that value is exceeded)
  1354                        ;  An overflow condition does NOT affect the BCD value stored.
  Fri Apr 24 2026  6:57                                                                                                    Page 31


