  1901                        ;
  1902                        ; MicroDrive Error codes
  1903                        ;       These are the error codes per the Hitachi MicroDrive documentation.
  1904                        ;       The codes are read after an error is returned from a command
  1905                        ;       by executing an IDE Get Status command from BIOS.
  1906                        ;
  1907                        ;The X register will contaim the error code as detailed below:
  1908                        ;
  1909                        ; Error Register:
  1910                        ;Bit 7 - CRC Error or Bad Block error
  1911                        ;Bit 6 - Uncorrectable Data Error
  1912                        ;Bit 5 - 0 (not used) MC (used for Removable-Media drives)
  1913                        ;Bit 4 - ID Not Found
  1914                        ;Bit 3 - 0 (not used) MCR (used for Removable-Media drives)
  1915                        ;Bit 2 - Aborted Command error
  1916                        ;Bit 1 - Track Zero not found error
  1917                        ;Bit 0 - Data Address Mark Not Found
  1918                        ;
  1919                        ; The codes are indexed here and as they are received, the appropriate
  1920                        ; error message will be displayed.
  1921                        ;
  1922                        IDE_ERROR_CODES
  1923                        ;
  1924 00:1D60: 80                   .DB     %10000000                       ;CRC or Bad Block
  1925 00:1D61: 40                   .DB     %01000000                       ;Uncorrectable Data Error
  1926 00:1D62: 10                   .DB     %00010000                       ;ID Not Found
  1927 00:1D63: 04                   .DB     %00000100                       ;Aborted Command
  1928 00:1D64: 02                   .DB     %00000010                       ;Track Zero not found
  1929 00:1D65: 01                   .DB     %00000001                       ;Data Address Mark not found
  1930                        ;
  1931                        ; IDE Error handler addresses
  1932                        ;       These are the addresses for the error messages.
  1933                        ;       These are indexed as above, so once the error message is matched
  1934                        ;       above, the index is multiplied by two and the address is used for the
  1935                        ;       error message text string.
  1936                        ;
  1937                        IDE_ERROR_ADDRESS
  1938                        ;
